        <title>Directional pad</title>
        <description>&lt;h2 id=&quot;introduction&quot;&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The navigation structure allows your to set defined areas within your application that can be controlled via the controller. This is achieved is by adding a &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;data-cwc-navgroup=&#39;*&#39;&lt;/code&gt; data attribute to your HTML markup allowing the &lt;strong&gt;cwc&lt;/strong&gt; object to register the group. The &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;*&lt;/code&gt; should represented the index of the navigation group starting from zero.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;data-cwc-navitem&lt;/code&gt; are used to define an item within the navigation group. Adding the value of &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;starting-point&lt;/code&gt; will allow you to set the main focus on where you wish to start the user when your aplliaction is loaded. Only one ‘starting-point’ can be set within your appliaction.&lt;/p&gt;

